title: Grateful Dead Live at Market Square Arena on 1976-10-01
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Mama Tried, Deal, Cassidy, Friend Of The Devil, Big River, Brown Eyed Women, It's All Over Now, Scarlet Begonias, Promised Land

Set 2

Might As Well, Samson & Delilah, Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Dancin' In The Streets-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Ship of Fools-> Dancin' In The Streets-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Love this show Dave, I provided the audience source for this show and have more info on it if you are interested.  Got it in a trade in 1987-8.  2nd-3d Gen (all Nak transfers).  Suffered from many spins over the years.  It came from a taper known to all.  It was recorded on Nagra RTR 7.5 IPS according to my notes.  Yeah, it was one of those 'Do Not Trade' tapes, but the statute has run on all that, & we all need to get over it.

great show(to me) cause i was there but... so special to me as one of my friends i sat next to is no longer with us but i know there r SO MANY great shows that have special meanings to all of us. just glad the full show is available to listen to. got a tape awhile back but was only the 2nd set. but(to me) killer Help on the Way/Slipknot/Franklins Tower. i know there r better versions out there but just so very special to me. RIP Brother Greg!! miss u so much...

Flake the Hoosier
Indiana 76' This is a excellent 76' show.The second set smokes and the sound quality is just stellar so thank you Dave for that.
